      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's a philosophical thing, but in a real debate, one side usually has a stronger logical foundation. some people say that a country can't even function if it doesn't have sovereignty first, so the humanitarian argument is basically secondary or even impossible to uphold without a stable border. do you see that as a valid point, or is that just an excuse to overlook human rights?",
